        "title": "feat(heartbeat): add config to preserve silent task results in agent context",
        "body": "<!--\r\nOptional linked context:\r\nAdd a visible `Closes #<issue-number>` or `Related: #<issue-number>` line\r\nbelow this comment.\r\n\r\nRequired PR title:\r\ntype: user-facing description\r\nUse a parenthesized scope only when it adds clarity:\r\nfix(auth): login redirect loops when session cookie is expired\r\n\r\nTypes: feat, fix, improve, refactor, docs, chore.\r\nFor fixes, describe the user-visible symptom and trigger:\r\nfix: task list fails to load when user has no environments\r\nAvoid implementation details such as:\r\nfix: add null check to task query\r\n-->\r\nCloses #95811 \r\n\r\n## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nThe `agents.defaults.heartbeat.ackMaxChars` config affected two unrelated behaviors:\r\n\r\n* Delivering a message to the user\r\n* Building the message history for the bot context\r\n\r\nThese behaviors should be configurable separately. This PR adds a new config field to decouple the behavior.\r\n\r\nConcretely, this allows users to avoid being notified when the bot completes a heartbeat task while still allowing the bot to retain what it did during that task in memory.\r\n<!--\r\nDescribe the concrete user, product, or operational problem.\r\nFor fixes, begin with:\r\n\"Fixes an issue where users <do X> would <experience Y> when <condition>.\"\r\nor:\r\n\"Resolves a problem where...\"\r\n\r\nName the affected UI surface or workflow. Do not describe the code-level cause here.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\nThis adds a config-gated heartbeat transcript mode that preserves the existing default behavior, while allowing users to keep only the final heartbeat result in future model context. Heartbeat poll prompts, tool calls, and tool results remain stripped in that mode, so background tasks can be remembered without notifying the user or bloating replay history.\r\n<!--\r\nIn one or two sentences, explain the complete shipped solution, key design\r\ndecisions, and relevant boundaries or non-goals. Include implementation detail\r\nonly when it helps reviewers understand user-visible behavior or risk.\r\nAvoid file-by-file narration.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\nUsers can run silent heartbeat tasks that produce useful results without being notified immediately, while still letting the agent remember those results for later follow-up. Existing heartbeat behavior remains unchanged by default.\r\n<!--\r\nState what users, operators, or developers can now do or expect. Lead with the\r\nconcrete benefit and use user-facing language. If there is no user-visible\r\nimpact, say so plainly.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n<img width=\"734\" height=\"164\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/abc7b5ef-77ff-4449-af21-b26e29a343c9\" />\r\n\r\nThis is after the PR. Before the PR, the bot would just answer that it cannot see any heartbeat task in the history.\r\n\r\n(Note: Specifically because it ends the task with HEARTBEAT_OK, but this is what I want - the bot compile interesting stuff and only tell me about it if I ask. I don't want it to message me after each run.)\r\n\r\nImage description:\r\n> User message: Was there any interesting result in your heartbeat task from 3 hours ago?\r\n> Bot message: Yeah! The 18:06 one had the Sega FY26 sales update — P3 Reload at 2.9M, P5R at 8.6M lifetime, Metaphor at 2.4M, LaD Infinite Wealth 2M, Sonic x Shadow 3M. Plus EA laying off more people ahead of the Saudi Arabia sale.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nShow the most useful proof that this change works. Screenshots, screencasts,\r\nterminal output, focused tests, CI results, live observations, redacted logs,\r\nand artifact links are all useful. Include before/after evidence for visual\r\nchanges when it clarifies the result.\r\n\r\nReviewers will inspect the code, tests, and CI. Use this section to make the\r\nvalidation easy to understand, not to restate the diff.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n\r\n* pnpm build: passed\r\n* pnpm check: 1 typecheck error, unrelated (was in main when I checked it out?) \r\n\r\n>src/config/sessions/session-accessor.ts:1545:46 - error TS6133: 'sessionStore' is declared but its value is never read.\r\n>1545   const { agentId, sessionEntry, sessionKey, sessionStore } =\r\n\r\n* pnpm test src/auto-reply/heartbeat-filter.test.ts --run: 38/38 passed successfully\r\n* pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-injection.test.ts --run : 10/10 passed successfully\r\n* Actual tests on local install by talking to the bot / looking at the requests' body to confirm all 3 config values behave as expected in practice (they do)\r\n\r\nNOTE: Human + AI-Assisted code, human tests",
